Klikor IDE Bridge ships a three-version marketplace ladder, mirroring upstream's own release channels
(upstream verifier surfaced that upstream main HEAD references `ActionTreeGroupUtil`, a class that only
exists on IntelliJ Platform 262/2026.2 -- see per-version notes below):

Klikor IDE Bridge 1.0.0 was forked from commit db611224b3dce5a111cc8051e550fefa7ea7125e ("Release 2025.1
version", the last state of the idea-plugin module that declared sinceBuild = 243), idea-plugin/
subdirectory only. It is published on the JetBrains Marketplace capped to build range 243-251.*.

Klikor IDE Bridge 1.1.0 is built from upstream commit 9005402dd78415b99f45e5220c0cbaef075b063a ("Update
plugin to support 2026.1 and upgrade dependencies", 2026-03-26) -- upstream's own "2026.1" Marketplace
release commit (pluginVersion = 2026.1, pluginSinceBuild = 252 there). This predates upstream's
platform-262 compatibility fix (`git log -S ActionTreeGroupUtil` pins that reference to commit 5af9d10,
2026-05-14, well after 9005402), so this build's ActionsTree.java does not reference the 262-only API.
It declares sinceBuild = 252, untilBuild = 261.* (capped -- see idea-plugin/gradle.properties for why)
and is published as the second Marketplace release channel, so 243-251.* IDEs resolve to 1.0.0, 252-261.*
IDEs resolve to 1.1.0, and 262+ IDEs resolve to 1.2.0.

Klikor IDE Bridge 1.2.0 re-syncs the idea-plugin/ subdirectory to upstream main at commit
9487e193c331cd9b53e7d504f85c446c769bc0ff ("add claude code action", 2026-05-29), which carries upstream's
platform-262 compatibility fix (ActionTreeGroupUtil). It declares sinceBuild = 262 (no until-build) and
is published as the third Marketplace release channel, so 262+ IDEs resolve to 1.2.0.

All three versions carry the identical Klikor rebrand (plugin id/name/vendor/description, focus-gating
default, and HTTP server log strings -- see the list of changed files in idea-plugin/build.gradle.kts,
idea-plugin/gradle.properties, idea-plugin/settings.gradle.kts, idea-plugin/.gitignore,
idea-plugin/src/main/java/com/jetbrains/ide/streamdeck/RemoteActionServer.java,
idea-plugin/src/main/java/com/jetbrains/ide/streamdeck/service/StreamDeckHttpService.kt,
idea-plugin/src/main/java/com/jetbrains/ide/streamdeck/settings/ActionServerConfigurable.java,
idea-plugin/src/main/java/com/jetbrains/ide/streamdeck/settings/ActionServerSettings.kt,
idea-plugin/src/main/java/com/jetbrains/ide/streamdeck/settings/StreamDeckPreferenceComponent.java,
idea-plugin/src/main/resources/META-INF/plugin.xml,
idea-plugin/src/main/resources/META-INF/pluginIcon.svg,
idea-plugin/src/main/resources/META-INF/pluginIcon_dark.svg -- applied identically at each version's
upstream base commit). The repo tree at any given time carries the source for ONE version (currently
1.2.0, the main-HEAD-based state); the 1.1.0 build is not checked into this repo as a second source tree
(see dist/ below) but is fully reproducible from the upstream base commit above plus this file list.

dist/klikor-ide-bridge-1.1.0.zip is the built 1.1.0 plugin artifact, kept here for release/upload
convenience since its source (upstream commit 9005402) isn't checked into this working tree. Rebuild it
by checking out 9005402's idea-plugin/ subdirectory, applying the file list above from this tree's git
history (or from a 1.1.0 tag once one exists), setting pluginVersion=1.1.0 / pluginSinceBuild=252 /
pluginUntilBuild=261.* in gradle.properties, and running `./gradlew buildPlugin` with a JDK 21 toolchain
(JBR 21, e.g. bundled with DataGrip 2025.3, or any JDK 21).

